Japanese: ラトラパントの街並み

ついに、ラトラパントまで
やってきたぜ！！
English: We're finally visiting Rattrapante!!

Japanese: 科学の都ラトラパント。
English: The capital city of science, Rattrapante.

Japanese:
みなよ。
古い建物に混じって、
近代的なビルがみえるだろ。
English: Everyone, here you can see old-fashioned buildings mixed in with modern ones.

Japanese:
科学と伝統が融合した
美しい街さ。
English: It's a beautiful city that merges science and tradition.

Japanese: ここにあるのは特工房だよな。
English: Plus, the Special Workshop is here.

Japanese:
できたばかりの工房だけど、
今や八工房の１つに
数える人もいるらしいぜ。
English: The workshop only just opened, but people are already counting it as one of the Eight Workshops.
Let's go and see for ourselves.

Japanese:
でも、特工房の人形師は
変人だっていう噂だよ。
English: But, there's a rumour that the Special Workshop's Puppet Maker is a bit eccentric.
Don't get carried away.
Welcome to the Special Workshop.
Thanks for having us.
(Oh! He's kind of a hottie.)

Japanese:
さっそく
工房を案内しましょう。
English: Let's start with a tour of the workshop.

Japanese: よろしくお願いします。
English: That sounds perfect.

Japanese:
なんだか
円工房に似た感じの
施設ですね。
English: This place reminds me of the Circle Workshop for some reason.

Japanese:
はい。
私はもともと円工房で
弟子をしていました。
English: Right. I was originally a student at the Circle Workshop.

Japanese:
今は独立して
自分の工房を開いた
というわけです。
English: Now I've gone independent and opened my own workshop.

Japanese:
じゃあ、
古臭い人形ばっかりなのか？
English: Then, you only make old-fashioned mechs?

Japanese:
せっかく
こんなとこまで
来たってのに……。
English: Even though we came all this way...

Japanese:
ケイ！
言葉に気をつけな！
English:
Kay!
Think before you speak!

Japanese:
ははは。
いいんですよ。
English:
Ha ha ha.
It's fine.

Japanese: 言いたいことはわかります。
English: I understand what he's saying.

Japanese:
私は、師匠とは違う考え方を
持っています。
English: I have a different way of thinking than my master.

Japanese:
古い手法にとらわれていては、
時代に取り残されるばかり。
English: If you stick to the old methods, you'll be left behind the times.

Japanese:
伝統技法に
最新の科学を融合させ、
全く新しい人形を作り出す。
English: But if you combine traditional techniques with the latest scientific developments, you can produce some really novel mechs.

Japanese: それが特工房なのです。
English: That is what the Special Workshop is all about.
Wow.

Japanese: 素晴らしいお考えです。
English: That's a wonderful idea.

Japanese:
特工房の人形デザインは、
他の工房と全く異なっています。
English: The mech designs at the Special Workshop are unlike any other.

Japanese:
奇妙なデザインだと言う人も
いるようですが……
English: There are people who say that the designs are strange...

Japanese:
しかし、あと１０年もすれば、
特工房のスタイルが一般的な
ものになることでしょう。
English: But, in 10 years time, the Special Workshop's style will be commonplace.

Japanese:
へぇ。
デザインに自信アリか。
English: Oh? So you're very confident in the design then?
He he he.

Japanese:
まだ工房を開いたばかりなので、
完成した人形は１種類だけ。
English: The workshop opened recently, so in terms of completed mechs, there's only 1 avaliable.

Japanese:
ですから、
今の時点ではコンセプトが
伝わりにくいですが……
English: Which makes it hard to convey my concept at this moment in time...

Japanese:
いずれ人形が増えてくれば、
私の目指すものがおわかり
いただけると思いますよ。
English: As more mechs are completed, I think you'll be able to understand just what it is I'm aiming for.

Japanese: 特工房の目指す/c5ロマン/c3がね。
English: The Special Workshop strives for /c5romance/c3.

Japanese: 開始イベント　終了
